name: Charlotte's Butternut Squash Fries
author: Charlotte C.
summary: This is my favorite side dish, and the first thing I've made all by myself. It goes great with pretty much anything and is a perfect side for a Thanksgiving dinner or just a cold fall day. Hope you enjoy!
ingredients: 1  butternut squash - peeled, seeded, and cut into strips
3 cloves garlic, minced, or more to taste
3 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves stripped, or more to taste
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C)
Mix squash, olive oil, paprika, garlic, thyme, and salt together in a bowl until evenly coated; spread in a single layer onto the prepared baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until squash is tender and lightly browned, 30 to 40 minutes
